Third Phase of Fifth Round of Six-Party Talks Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Beijing, February 13 (KCNA) -- The third phase of the fifth round of the six-party talks took place in Beijing from February 8 to 13. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks that proceeded in a sincere atmosphere discussed the ways of denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks the parties decided to offer economic and energy aid equivalent to one million tons of heavy fuel oil in connection with the DPRK's temporary suspension of the operation of its nuclear facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And the DPRK and the United States agreed to solve their pending issues and kick off the bilateral talks aimed at opening full diplomatic ties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the just-concluded talks the parties agreed to have the sixth round of the six-party talks in the future.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Putin 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by Russian President Vladimir Vladimirovich Putin on the occasion of his birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was conveyed by Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Valery E. Sukhinin to an official concerned on Feb. 12.

Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Russia  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- The famous work of Kim Jong Il "The Workers' Party of Korea Organizes and Guides All the Victories of Our People" was brought out in booklet by the Nakhodka Publishing and Printing House of Russia on Feb. 9. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on Oct. 3, Juche 79 (1990), clarifies the idea that the party leadership is a sure guarantee for the victory of the socialist cause, the issue of developing the WPK into a revolutionary party of Juche type and basic ways for the WPK to fulfill its mission and duty as a leading political organization, etc.

February Holiday Celebrated  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- Meetings, a book and photo exhibition, film shows, round-table talks and a reading session were held in Laos, France, Egypt and Ethiopia from Feb. 2 to 5 on the occasion of the February holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the events were famous works of the peerlessly great men, photos showing their undying exploits and books and photos introducing the Korean people engaged in socialist construction and in the struggle to achieve national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the film shows watched Korean film "February 16, the Greatest National Holiday." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Khamphan Sittidampha, secretary of the Central Committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Youth Union, in a speech at a meeting referred to the decision of the International Kim Il Sung Prize Council to award "International Kim Il Sung Prize" to Kim Jong Il and warmly hailed it on behalf of the Lao youth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Guy Dupre, secretary general of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea, at a meeting highly praised Kim Jong Il who has firmly defended the DPRK's sovereignty and ensured peace on the Korean Peninsula and the Asian region and wisely led the Korean people in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful nation and achieve the country's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Youssef Amin Wali, vice-chairman of the National Democratic Party of Egypt, at round-table talks said that Kim Jong Il is successfully carrying forward the cause of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tatek Kassa, chairperson of the Addis Ababa Youth Association of Ethiopia, at a reading session stressed that not only the Korean people but other peoples of the world highly praise Kim Jong Il as the son of guerrillas.

Association for Supporting Songun Politics Formed in Nepal 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the Nepalese Association for Supporting the Songun Politics was held in Dulikel City on Feb. 6 on the occasion of the February holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Manik Lama was elected chairman of the association and a declaration was made public at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that sovereignty and dignity are dearest to all the countries and peoples, the declaration said the association would disseminate the Songun politics among the Nepalese and help them deeply understand the country's dignity and sovereignty on the basis of its reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The association will organize multifarious events on the Songun politics and self-reliance on the major occasions in Nepal and on occasions of weighty importance in boosting the ties of friendship between the two countries, the declaration said, adding that it would actively join in the international movement for support and solidarity with the Songun politics and the anti-imperialist cause of the Korean people.

Collection of Anecdotes about Music "General and Songs" Vol. 2 Sees Light  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- The Literature and Art Publishing House recently brought out a collection of anecdotes about music "General and Songs" Vol. 2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The five-part book contains 116 impressive anecdotes about music telling how energetically Kim Jong Il guided the music creation including the creation, representation and dissemination of songs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first part of the book includes touching anecdotes dealing with the extraordinary wisdom and tireless leadership of Kim Jong Il who led the musicians to make songs lauding the brilliant revolutionary life, undying revolutionary exploits and noble virtues of President Kim Il Sung reverberate more loudly throughout the country just as "Song of General Kim Il Sung" and "General Kim Il Sung Is Our Sun" do. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The second part of the book carries anecdotes dating back to the period when a lot of songs reflecting the spirit of devotedly defending the leader and songs in praise of the motherland such as "For the Motherland," "Song of Airman" and "Blue Sky over My Country" loved by the servicepersons and people were produced and widely disseminated thanks to Kim Jong Il's noble intention and under his guidance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The third part of the book contains anecdotes dealing with the creation of famous songs including those explaining that Kim Jong Il, genius of music and arts, propounded the idea that music is humanics and gave a clear-cut definition of famous songs for the first time in history and guided singers to present the songs to meet the need of their melodies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fourth and fifth parts of the book tell how wisely he led the creators and artistes to make all the songs created in the Songun era resound as marches encouraging the servicepersons and people of the DPRK to win victory after victory and give full play to their talents and skills.

Floral Basket to Kim Jong Il from Lao President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a floral basket by Lao President Choummaly Saynasone, general secretary of the C.C., the Lao People's Revolutionary Party, on the occasion of his birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was conveyed to an official concerned Monday by Phonekham Inthaboualy, Lao charge d'affaires a.i. here.

Agricultural Workers Celebrate February Holiday  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- A meeting of agricultural workers and a performance of the 35th National Art Festival of Agricultural Workers were held at the Ponghwa Art Theatre on Feb. 12 on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea Central Committee Kim Jung Rin and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An address by Kang Chang Uk, chairman of the Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea, was followed by speeches at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter of pledge to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An art performance was given by members of art groups from different farms which presented art pieces of ideological and artistic value to the national art festival of agricultural workers held on the occasion of the February holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In their ode and chorus, a female trio and chorus, a chorus and other numbers the performers sang high praises of the greatness of Kim Jong Il and best wishes of the agricultural workers and other Korean people for him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also staged numbers dealing with the great changes that have taken place in the socialist countryside and the worthwhile life the agricultural workers enjoy while cultivating co-op fields.

Russian Musicians Give Performance on Occasion of February Holiday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- A performance was given by a Russian musician and his party at the Moranbong Theatre on Feb. 12 on the occasion of the February holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Appearing as guest stars at the performance were artistes of the Merited State Chorus of the Korean People's Army, the State Symphony Orchestra, the Mansudae Art Troupe and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fourth movement "Glory to General Kim Jong Il" of the symphony suite "Long Journey for Songun Leadership" and orchestra "Rich Harvest Comes to the Chongsan Plain" presented by Korean artistes were conducted by People's Artiste Leonid Nikolayev, professor at the Moscow Tchaikovsky State Conservatory in Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In orchestra "Congratulations" created by Russian composer Nikolai Druzenkov on the occasion of the February holiday and orchestra and chorus "Nostalgia," famous masterpiece, for piano solo presented by pianist Sergei Musayelan who is international concours winner and merited artiste, the performers successfully represented the ideological and artistic value of the pieces with their refined rendition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also staged world famous music pieces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were Minister of Culture Kang Nung Su and officials concerned.

Receptions Given in Celebration of February Holiday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Valery E. Sukhinin hosted a reception at the embassy on Monday on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian ambassador said in his speech that Kim Jong Il is well known to the Russian people as an outstanding statesman, leader of the party, army and people of the DPRK and a close friend of the Russian people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the Russia-DPRK joint declaration, the Moscow declaration, the Russia-DPRK treaty of friendship, good neighborliness and cooperation adopted at a series of meetings between the top leaders of the two countries serve as a solid foundation for reenergizing the Russia-DPRK cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are waging a dynamic drive to implement the tasks set forth in the joint editorial in the DPRK for this year under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop in his speech said that it is the invariable stand of the DPRK government to steadily boost the DPRK-Russia friendly and cooperative relations in many aspects, hoping that Russia, the DPRK's neighbor, would achieve successes in the efforts to increase its national defence capability and achieve social stability and economic progress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Jalaleddin Namini Mianji, Iranian ambassador to the DPRK, and Ahmed Medhat, military attache of the Egyptian embassy here, hosted receptions each on the same day on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il.

Russian Orthodox Church Presents Vehicles to Kochang Co-op Farm
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- The Russian Orthodox Church presented vehicles to the Korea-Russia Friendship Kochang Co-op Farm. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Valery E. Sukhinin handed over the vehicles to the farm at a meeting Monday. Present there were Ryu Sung Rim, vice-chairman of the Korea-Russia Friendship Association, officials of the farm and staff members of the Russian embassy in Pyongyang.

Highly-efficient Agricultural Biomedicine Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- The Koryo Biomedicine Center of the Branch Academy of Biology under the DPRK State Academy of Sciences has developed a new kind of highly-efficient and cheap agricultural biomedicine. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an organic agricultural medicine made from the proper mixture of extracts of various plants, nutrients, growth promoting and active materials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It helps growth of seedlings and germination of crops and other plants and shortens their harvest time, prevents crops from being damaged by blight and harmful insects and considerably improves the quality of products. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its production cost is one third of formalin and iron sulphate. It, water-soluble contact agent, does not harm to human, farm crops, domestic animals and fishes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is widely introduced in production on co-op farms.

Beautiful Scenery of Secret Camp in Mt. Paektu
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- The visitors to the Secret Camp in Mt. Paektu, the birth place of Kim Jong Il, marvel at its beautiful scenes in February. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is most wonderful is the frostwork. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The needle-leaved trees in rows along the roads are dressed with frosts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The trees, bushes and mosses on cliffs of Jong Il Peak rising imposingly as well as the sunrise rock, fleet-steed rock and general's rock are all covered with frosts. They present a silver-white world like a illusory one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sun rises over the sunrise rock, turning Jong Il Peak red and the flying frost in Sobaeksu Valley shines brightly in various colors and some times forms rainbows. This scenery leads the viewers to ecstasy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though knee-deep snow is heaped on the banks of the stream, the Sobaek Stream with the headspring in Mt. Sobaek is meandering down around the secret camp. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The snow-capped large and small stones in the stream look like polar bears. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Snowstorm on Jong Il Peak forms the acme of the snow-covered landscape of the secret camp. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The snowstorm on the peak like a lighthouse on the sea of the Paektu forests presents a spectacular sight. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Willow trees on the banks of the Sobaek Stream near the native home have opened catkins some time ago, delighting the visitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The mysterious beauty of the secret camp adds luster to the greatness of the peerlessly illustrious commander Kim Jong Il.

U.S. Arms Buildup under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- The United States recently carried out a test-fire of a new-type Tomahawk missile. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no doubt that when it is deployed for action, the offensive capacity of the U.S. against its adversary will increase, notes the analyst of Minju Joson Tuesday, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This new-type cruise missile is said to increase the combat capability of warships and markedly shorten the time of the approach of the missile to the objects as it, unlike the former Tomahawk, can take another sight at a new target appearing while in flight. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This shows that the U.S. is making desperate efforts for the qualitative improvement of offensive capacity and increase of "defense capacity." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not because there is any worry about its security matter that the U.S. is getting overheated in the development of a new cruise missile and establishment of the missile defense system (MD). Truth to tell, a military entity threatening the security of the U.S. is nowhere to be seen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. connects everything related to the MD with the DPRK. By finalizing the MD targeted against the DPRK it seeks to lay a foundation for a preemptive attack and, through it, establish its military control over the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The hectic push of the U.S. for the MD is a serious criminal act of gravely threatening and wrecking peace and security on the Korean Peninsula and other parts of the world and leading to a new arms race. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With no amount of artifice can the U.S. conceal its true colors as the chief criminal fostering and aggravating the new arms race and harassing world peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. would be well advised to stop at once its arms buildup, pondering over the catastrophic consequences it would entail.

U.S. Trounced for Going against Dialogue
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- The U.S. is deploying ultra-modern military hardware in south Korea, Japan and other areas around the Korean Peninsula while intensifying offensive military exercises targeted against the DPRK. Branding this as a deliberate and premeditated act to push the situation on the peninsula to the brink of a war, a Rodong Sinmun analyst Tuesday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is self-evident that it is impossible to expect sound negotiations in the war atmosphere and, even if negotiations are held, they cannot substantially contribute to ensuring peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Contacts and talks through various channels are now underway for the settlement of the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula. It can not but be an open denial of dialogue and harassment of peace for the U.S. warlike forces to escalate military threat to the DPRK while massively shipping the ultra-modern military hardware to areas around the peninsula at this time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. attitude of whetting sword for aggression behind the scene while paying lip-service to a negotiated solution to the issue is a criminal act aimed at hindering and scuttling the dialogue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent stand of the U.S. to carry its Asian strategy into practice with the Korean Peninsula as the springboard. It intends to realize its ambition to dominate Asia by implementing its Korea strategy through a preemptive nuclear attack and expanding the war beyond the boundary of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The daily escalating moves of the U.S. to provoke a new war in Korea compel the people of the DPRK to bolster military deterrent to defend the country's sovereignty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. would be held fully accountable for the serious consequences to be entailed by its reckless moves for a war of aggression against the DPRK.

Floral Basket and Congratulatory Card to Kim Jong Il from Vietnam Defence Ministry
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a floral basket and a congratulatory card by the Ministry of Defence of Vietnam on the occasion of his birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floral basket and congratulatory card were conveyed by the deputy director of the Foreign Relations Department of the ministry to the DPRK ambassador to Vietnam on Feb. 9.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Iranian Ambassador
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a talk with Iranian Ambassador to the DPRK Jalaleddin Namini Mianji when the latter paid a farewell call on him at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Yong Il, other officials and staff members of the Iranian embassy here.

Foreign Guests Here
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 13 (KCNA) -- Alva Chavez, member of the International Kim Il Sung Prize Council, and a delegation of the Mongolian Mt. Paektu Association for Independent Development led by its Executive Chairman E. Maksim arrived here Tuesday on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Players from Bulgaria, Belarus, Switzerland, Ukraine and Uzbekistan also arrived here today to participate in the 16th International Figure-skating Festival for Paektusan Cup to be held on the occasion of the February holiday.
